10~DTP*304*D8*99990101~EB*F**98******S7*15~HSD*VS*1***34*36~MSG*Limited to unrestored permanent molars.~EB*F**CO******S7*15~MSG*Covered only when necessary to replace prematurely lost or extracted deciduous teeth.~MSG*Limited to initial appliance only, limited to one bilateral, per arch, or one unilateral per quadrant. Covered once per lifetime.~EB*F**60******S7*13~MSG*Covered only when needed to inhibit thumb sucking; initial appliance only.~EB*F************AD:D1550~EB*F**4~HSD*VS*1***34*60~MSG*Fourteen or more individual x-rays, including bitewings, performed on the same date will receive the benefit of a full mouth series of x-rays.~EB*F**1~MSG*Covered up to the maximum allowable amount of a full mouth series.~EB*F**30~HSD*VS*1***34*12~DTP*304*D8*20250521~DTP*304*D8*20250521~MSG*Limited to either a maximum of 4 bitewing films or a set (7-8 films) of vertical bitewings.~EB*F**96~HSD*VS*1***34*24~HSD*VS*1***34*24~DTP*304*D8*20250521~DTP*304*D8*20250521~DTP*304*D8*20250521~DTP*304*D8*20250521~DTP*304*D8*20250521~DTP*304*D8*20250521~DTP*304*D8*20250521~DTP*304*D8*20250521~DTP*304*D8*20250521~MSG*Covered when done more than 12 months after the insertion of the original denture.~MSG*Covered when done more than 12 months after the insertion of the original denture.~EB*F**7~MSG*Anesthesia (D9222, D9223, D9230, D9239, D9243, D9248) is covered when performed with 3 or more covered non-surgical extractions performed on the same day or any covered surgical service.~MSG*Anesthesia (D9222, D9223, D9230, D9239, D9243, D9248) is covered on children under age 8 when performed with five or more covered procedures (consisting of cdt codes D2140-D7991), in two separate quadrants, performed on the same day.~EB*F**40~EB*F**68~MSG*Plan does not limit surfaces of composite restorations.~MSG*Posterior resin-based composite restorations (white fillings) (D2391-D2394) receive the alternate benefit of an amalgam restoration (silver filling) (D2140-D2161).~EB*F**AQ~MSG*Covered when there is a liability.~EB*I************AD:D4381~EB*F**35~MSG*Claims must be submitted within fifteen months from the date of service in order to be considered.~MSG*Dental prostheses needed to replace teeth missing prior to being insured with this Guardian plan are not covered unless the tooth was extracted while covered by the prior plan.~MSG*Guardian's pandemic support program will cover exams, cleanings and fluoride treatments twice per calendar year between 07/01/2020 and 12/31/2021. All other plan provisions apply.~MSG*In order to evaluate the coverage for this treatment and respond as quickly as possible, we must receive supporting diagnostic materials, such as diagnostic intraoral photographs, radiographs and/or chart notes about the claim.~MSG*Please submit as soon as possible so we can process the claim accurately.~EB*F************AD:D9310~HSD*VS*1***34*12~MSG*Per dental specialty; covered when no other treatment, other than radiographic images, is performed during the same visit.~EB*F**36~HSD*VS*1***21*5~MSG*Clinical review required for crowns  (includes onlays, veneers, post & cores and buildups). Submission must include diagnostic pre-operative x-ray, patient chart notes and any relevant intraoral photographs.~MSG*Single crowns (D2710, D2712, D2720-D2722, D2740, D2750-D2753, D2780-D2783, D2790-D2792, D2794).~MSG*Includes veneers; when the appliance is no longer useable.~EB*F************AD:D2950~MSG*Considered in conjunction with a covered unit of crown or bridge and only when necessitated by substantial loss of natural tooth structure.~EB*F**26~HSD*VS*1***32*1~MSG*Applies to D3110, D3120. Considered part of the restoration.~EB*F**73~HSD*VS*1***32*1~MSG*Endodontic therapy, root canal treatment and retreatment (D3310, D3320, D3330, D3331, D3332, D3333, D3346, D3347, D3348) is covered once per tooth per lifetime.~EB*F************AD:D9110~HSD*VS*1***34*6~MSG*Also applies to D9440; covered when no other treatment, other than x-rays is performed during the same visit.~EB*F************AD:D0140~HSD*VS*1***34*6~DTP*304*D8*99990101~MSG*Covered if no other treatment, other than radiographic images, is performed in the same visit.~EB*I************AD:D0160~DTP*304*D8*99990101~EB*F**BY~HSD*VS*1***34*6~DTP*304*D8*20250521~MSG*Oral evaluations, including codes D0120, D0145, D0150, D0170, D0180 or D9430.~EB*I************AD:D0431~EB*F************AD:D9944~HSD*VS*1***32*1~MSG*Also applies to D9945; when performed within 6 months after osseous surgery.~EB*F**24~MSG*Clinical review required for periodontal scaling and root planing .  Submission must include diagnostic pre-operative x-rays (not panorex) and periodontal charting.~EB*F************AD:D4341~HSD*VS*1***34*24~DTP*304*D8*99990101~MSG*Also applies to D4342; covered per quadrant where there is radiographic and pocket charting evidence of bone loss.~EB*F**9******S8*12~HSD*VS*1***34*6~DTP*304*D8*99990101~DTP*304*D8*99990101~MSG*Adult prophylaxis (D1110) is covered age 12 and over.~MSG*Either one regular prophylaxis or a periodontal maintenance procedure~EB*F**80~HSD*VS*1***21*5~MSG*When the appliance is no longer useable.~EB*F**GY~HSD*VS*1***21*5~MSG*Applies to post and cores; when no longer useable.~EB*F**39~HSD*VS*1***21*5~MSG*Applies to dentures and bridges; when the appliance is no longe r useable.~EB*F**64******S7*18~HSD*VS*1***34*12~EB*F**64******S8*19~HSD*VS*1***34*36~EB*F************AD:D4355~HSD*VS*1***34*36~MSG*Covered when no preventive, diagnostic, periodontal service or periodontal surgery has been performed in the previous 36 month period or the same day.~MSG*Full mouth debridement (D4355) and prophy/perio maintenance rendered on the same day are considered inclusive and allowed as D4355, when the benefit is allowable. Comprehensive periodontal eval (D0180) is not covered on the same day as an allowed D4355~EB*F**95~HSD*VS*1***32*1~MSG*Applies to D4263, D4264, D4266, D4267 services must be performed on the same day and tooth must be present.~EB*F************AD:D4346~HSD*VS*1***34*24~HSD*VS*1***34*36~DTP*304*D8*99990101~DTP*304*D8*99990101~MSG*Inclusive of frequency limit for prophylaxis/periodontal maintenance procedures, must be performed more than 12 months after D1110 or D4910.~MSG*Considered when no perio procedures in history, except D4355 full mouth debridement, no prior prophylaxis within previous 12 months, no prophylaxis or periodontal procedure performed on same date.~EB*I**4~MSG*Cone beams (D0364, D0365, D0366, D0367).~EB*I************AD:D1354~EB*I************AD:D0460~EB*F**71~HSD*VS*1***34*24~MSG*Considered to be part of a permanent restoration; subject to 10 year replacement limitation if permanent restoration is placed after 24 months.~SE*380*0001~GE*1*504073336~IEA*1*504073336~